        <section class="col8 body"><h1>§ 42–602. Deeds of corporations; formal requisites; acknowledgment.</h1> <section class="content"><section><section class="line-group primary-content"><p>The deed of a corporation shall be executed and acknowledged either (1) by an attorney-in-fact appointed for that purpose or (2) without appointment, by its president or a vice-president if also attested by the secretary or assistant secretary of the corporation.</p></section><br/><section class="line-group annotations"><p>
      (<a class="internal-link" href="/dc/council/code/sections/42-602">Mar. 3, 1901, 31 Stat. 1268, ch. 854, § 497</a>; June 30, 1902, 32 Stat. 531, ch. 1329; <a class="internal-link" href="/dc/council/laws/10-110.html">Apr. 27, 1994, D.C. Law 10-110, § 2(c), 41 DCR 1023</a>.)
    </p><h4>Prior Codifications</h4><p>1981 Ed., § 45-502.</p><p>1973 Ed., § 45-302.</p><h4>Section References</h4><p>This section is referenced in § <a class="internal-link" href="/dc/council/code/sections/42-401">42-401</a> and § <a class="internal-link" href="/dc/council/code/sections/42-404">42-404</a>.</p><h4>Cross References</h4><p>Effective date of deeds, see § <a class="internal-link" href="/dc/council/code/sections/42-401">42-401</a>.</p><p>Failures in formal requisites of an instrument, fraudulent acts, see § <a class="internal-link" href="/dc/council/code/sections/42-404">42-404</a>.</p></section></section></section></section>
